4:05\n\n[ž≤®Ž∂ÄŪĆĆžĚľ ž†ēŽ≥ī]\nž≤®Ž∂ÄŪĆĆžĚľ: žóÜžĚĆ\n\n[Ž≥łŽ¨ł]\nAs you get comfortable with Claude, here are 5 easy techniques that can \n\ntransform your experience from good to great.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nGetting better results with Claude\n\n\n\n <https://claude.ai>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nHi there,\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAs you get comfortable with Claude, here are 5 easy techniques that can \n\ntransform your experience from good to great:\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n1. Ask Claude to think out loud: When you need help with something complext, \n\ntry: "Think through this step-by-step" or "Break this down into smaller steps."\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n 2. Be specific when results are too vague: If Claude\'s response isn\'t quite \n\nwhat you need, add more detail: "That\'s helpful, but I need ideas specifically \n\nfor a family vacation with teenagers, not young children."\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n 3. Refine through conversation: Treat Claude as your creative partner and \n\nshape the output together: "I like where this email draft is going, could you \n\nmake it more casual and half as long?"\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n4. Specify your audience and tone: "Explain investing to a teenager" will get \n\nvery different results than just "Explain investing."\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe more you talk to Claude like a thoughtful collaborator, the better your \n\nresults will be!\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nTalk to Claude  <https://claude.ai>\n\n\n\n‚ÄĒ The Anthropic Team\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n <https://www.anthropic.com/?utm_source=email>\n\n\n\n <https://x.com/anthropicai>  \n\n<https://www.linkedin.com/company/anthropicresearch> \n\n<https://www.youtube.com/@anthropic-ai>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u200a\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThis email was sent to gpttitti@hansung.ac.kr. Unsubscribe \n\n<https://links.iterable.com/s/u/qqHzVNlMeC_05uh5zQiS5EwW7ECfvcM9PB-7N_-_40u2aqb_6IcBwdUi6PneDo9foo2OvvnZSfF0Si1ePQKoxCElvdFMyz2uuz2X3KAZ5eFhAd-lfU3FfdrsGb9XV3lAfTMEnYEfvLfJzFegf2ZthRa2FGYFiEXwR1rgr30GPaB0BVdBxhXTvTWHiRz8_xNN3P6SAkGPdT8dWf_k8GSrgfheSH4V_a2t6-yB0